The paper proposes a new model for multivariate time series classification, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the proposed models are efficient for complex tasks such as activity recognition or action recognition. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Attention LSTM, which is a neural network architecture commonly used in natural language processing, suggesting a possible connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed models, which could be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
